  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you take the attack action with a melee weapon, you can use your bonus action to have all weapon attacks you make be under the effects of Chakra Strike at 2nd level (Max of 3 attacks), and have each successful hit impose a Strength saving throw, where failure causes the creature to gain 1 rank of Weakened.</p><p> Once your attack action ends, the creature is knocked back a number of feet equal to 10 times the number of successful attacks.</p><p> You can use this style a number of times equal to half your proficiency bonus, rounded up, per long rest.</p><p> Ex-Cross Slash: You can use the Ex-Cross Slash even if you have expended all uses of this style.</p><p> When you use this style, you increase the number of attacks you make with the attack action by +2, and Chakra Strike applies to up to 5 attacks.</p><p></p>",
